cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.AI. 

The paper focuses on incorporating textual information into graph embeddings, which is a common topic in natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new framework for graph embedding, which involves sampling strategies and inductive learning, indicating that it may fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also evaluates its proposed framework on link prediction tasks, which is a common task in information retrieval (IR) and social networks analysis, suggesting that it may also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
